    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter May 3rd with a lineup heavily incentivized by stolen base upside and favorable SP xERA matchups. The clear priority start today is **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (82.13), who sits at the top of our efficiency rankings. Facing the right-handed Me. Kelly, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits from a massive 18% SP skill boost and an 87% stolen base success rate against a slower delivery, mitigating the usual inefficiency of his 8-hole placement. **Junior Caminero** (75.14) also demands attention; despite a park factor penalty, he is perfectly positioned in the 2-hole to exploit Mahle\u2019s 4.60 xERA, making him the anchor for our middle infield output. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** (67.99) remains a high-floor play atop the lineup against Paddack, providing the necessary speed-to-base-percentage ratio we prioritize in our 5x5 format.\n\nWe are keeping a close watch on **Yordan Alvarez** (63.71), whose elite 0.430 xwOBA keeps him in the lineup despite a sub-optimal platoon matchup against the lefty Suarez. Our most difficult decision on the bench was **Jerar Encarnacion** (41.97), who narrowly missed the cut. While his platoon advantage against Matz is theoretically attractive, his lower base projection and the density of high-efficiency starts from **Colt Keith** (66.91)\u2014who benefits from a rare \"slow delivery\" boost to his stolen base potential\u2014made him the odd man out. We continue to manage our remaining roster depth with **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar** remaining sidelined on the IL, placing higher pressure on **Carson Benge** (60.78) to capitalize on a favorable matchup against Kochanowicz to maintain our weekly volume.",
